Gombe State Governor Muhammadu Yahaya, has revealed that prayers from clerics like the General Overseer of the Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG), Pastor Enoch Adeboye, have been sustaining Nigeria. The governor disclosed this on Friday after receiving Adeboye who visited the state for his reach-out campaign titled; ‘light up eight city crusade’, organised to celebrate his 80th birthday. Yahaya who was represented by his Deputy, Dr. Manassah Jatau, said, “with the rate at which Nigeria is filled with misfortunes of insecurity, economic hardships, one can only believe that it is the prayers of the people like Pastor Adeboye that are sustaining the nation. Adeboye’s Son Says He’s Waiting For Criticism Ahead… Adeboye Releases Eight Prophecies For 2022 “Prayers can never be enough, we solicit for more prayers towards sustainable peace, unity, and progress.” Recall that Adeboye also announced upcoming commissioning of a dialysis centre at the Abubakar Tafawa Balewa Teaching Hospital, Bauchi to mark his 80th birthday, on March 2, 2022.